race.comment: Tough to assess away from the top contenders. FARISHA (7) brings narrow defeats from here at Wodonga last time. She will push forward and has the winkers on again. Comes back 200m briefly freshened and finds a winnable assignment. MONT SAINT MICHEL (3) resumed here in the same race as the above beaten 1L and then was only 2L drift at Echuca also over this trip. Presents fitter and doubt there's much between this pair. KYOKUSHIN (1) has a wide gate to deal with but is best on the fresh side and his best form would have him in the finish. The betting will guide with him.  DUDANCE (9) impressed missing a whisker at Kilmore first-up but has been plainer the two since. Kept on the fresh side and she can't be ignored. UGLY NICOS (5) is finding it hard to win but has been within range both starts this preparation and maps well. May enjoy the longer sprint now.
